{"title_page": "Salisu Buhari", "text_new": "{{multiple issues|{{Copy edit|date=March 2020}}\n{{POV|date=September 2014}}}}\n\n'''Salisu Buhari''' is a former Speaker of The House of the [[House of Representatives (Nigeria)|House of Representatives of Nigeria]]. In 1999, he resigned from office over the allegations of certificate forgery. He was later convicted of certificate forgery and sentenced to two years in prison with an option of fine. He paid the fine and was later pardoned by President [[Olusegun Obasanjo]].\n\n==Political Career==\nBuhari had been a businessman. In 1999, Buhari was the speaker of the [[House of Representatives (Nigeria)|Nigeria House of Representatives]], which placed him in the 4th highest office in Nigeria. However, this only lasted for six weeks before his [[University of Toronto]] scandal and the beginning of what was known as the University of Toronto Saga. The scandal ultimately led to his resignation and prosecution.\n\n==Controversies==\nThe news of his age and certificate forgery first broke out on 16 February 1999 by an investigative news publication, [[TheNews magazine]]. Their investigation concluded that Buhari was born in 1970 and not 1963 as he claimed, and also that he did not graduate from the University of Toronto. The article published about the speaker dispelled that the speaker did not attended the university, not to talk of graduating. Section 65(1) of the 1999 Constitution of the Federal Republic of Nigeria disqualifies anyone below the age of 30 from running for membership of the House of Representatives.\n\nBuhari had also claimed that he completed his '''[[National Youth Service Corps|National Youth Service]]''' at Standard Construction in [[Kano]] which was also not true, as his name could not be found on any record in the list of those who completed the scheme. When Buhari was confronted with multiple allegations about his declaration and falsification, he promptly responded accusing the publications as an attack on him and proclaims his innocence and threatened to file a lawsuit against the publisher for libel. His confidence and response to the allegations were very assertive in nature and quite convincing that he was a victim of a witch-hunt. The magazine had written to the University of Toronto, requesting confirmation that Buhari was an alumnus. In response, Carlo Villanueva, an official of the Institution wrote, \u201c''Regarding your request for confirmation of degree for Mr Ibrahim Salisu Buhari. We have searched our records and could not find anybody with the name you are inquiring with.''\u201d\n\nHe had been found guilty in the court of public opinion and among in the halls where policies are made and sentences are meted out, the tension had reached a fever pitch.\n\nIn 23 July 1999, disgraced and cornered, Buhari faced [[Nigerians]] and admitted to falsifying his age and forging certificates as well as other contents of the News report.\n\n\u201c''I apologize to you. I apologize to the nation. I apologize to my family and friends for all the distress I have caused them. I was misled in error by zeal to serve the nation, I hope the nation will forgive me and give me the opportunity to serve again.''\u201d\n\nHe resigned from his membership of the House of Representatives in 1999.\n\nIn 2013, he was chosen as part of the governing council of the [[University of Nigeria]] by the [[Federal government of Nigeria|Nigerian government]].<ref name=\"saharareporters\">{{cite news|url=http://saharareporters.com/2013/07/05/salisu-buhari-member-unn-governing-council-no-please|title=Salisu Buhari, A Member of UNN Governing Council? No Please!|last=Igbokwe|first=Joe|date=5 July 2013|work=[[Sahara Reporters]]|accessdate=5 September 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"nigeriapoliticsonline\">{{cite web|url=http://nigeriapoliticsonline.com/tinubu-guilty-of-certificate-forgery-like-salisu-buhari-obasanjo/|title=Tinubu guilty of certificate forgery like Salisu Buhari  &#8211;Obasanjo|date=14 August 2013|website=Nigeria Politics Online|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140905053505/http://nigeriapoliticsonline.com/tinubu-guilty-of-certificate-forgery-like-salisu-buhari-obasanjo/|archivedate=5 September 2014|url-status=dead|accessdate=5 September 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"9jabook\">{{cite web|url=http://www.9jabook.com/forum/topics/disgraced-fmr-speaker-salisu-buhari-of-toronto-university-forged-|title=Disgraced Fmr Speaker Salisu Buhari of &quot;Toronto University forged certificate&quot;  Now in UNN Governing council|date=4 April 2013|website=9jabook|accessdate=5 September 2014}}</ref>{{Unreliable source?|date=July 2018}}<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/africa/401123.stm|title=World: Africa {{!}} Nigerian speaker quits in tears|date=22 July 1999|work=[[BBC News]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thescoopng.com/abati-defends-appointment-of-certificate-forger-salisu-buhari-as-unn-governing-council-member/|title=Abati defends appointment of certificate forger, Salisu Buhari, as UNN governing council member|last=Lawal|first=Dare|date=14 April 2013|website=The ScoopNG}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}https://www.pulse.ng/gist/pop-culture/the-story-of-salisu-buhari-and-the-toronto-university-saga-id8022958.html\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Buhari, Salisu}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:University of Nigeria, Nsukka people]]\n", "text_old": "{{multiple issues|{{Copy edit|date=March 2020}}\n{{POV|date=September 2014}}}}\n\n'''Salisu Buhari''' is a former speaker of the [[House of Representatives (Nigeria)|House of Representatives of Nigeria]]. In 1999, he resigned from office over the allegations of certificate forgery. He was later convicted of certificate forgery and sentenced to two years in prison with an option of fine. He paid the fine and was later pardoned by President [[Olusegun Obasanjo]].\n\n==Political Career==\nBuhari had been a businessman. In 1999, Buhari was the speaker of the [[House of Representatives (Nigeria)|Nigeria House of Representatives]], which placed him in the 4th highest office in Nigeria. However, this only lasted for six weeks before his [[University of Toronto]] scandal and the beginning of what was known as the University of Toronto Saga. The scandal ultimately led to his resignation and prosecution.\n\n==Controversies==\nThe news of his age and certificate forgery first broke out on 16 February 1999 by an investigative news publication, [[TheNews magazine]]. Their investigation concluded that Buhari was born in 1970 and not 1963 as he claimed, and also that he did not graduate from the University of Toronto. The article published about the speaker dispelled that the speaker did not attended the university, not to talk of graduating. Section 65(1) of the 1999 Constitution of the Federal Republic of Nigeria disqualifies anyone below the age of 30 from running for membership of the House of Representatives.\n\nBuhari had also claimed that he completed his '''[[National Youth Service Corps|National Youth Service]]''' at Standard Construction in [[Kano]] which was also not true, as his name could not be found on any record in the list of those who completed the scheme. When Buhari was confronted with multiple allegations about his declaration and falsification, he promptly responded accusing the publications as an attack on him and proclaims his innocence and threatened to file a lawsuit against the publisher for libel. His confidence and response to the allegations were very assertive in nature and quite convincing that he was a victim of a witch-hunt. The magazine had written to the University of Toronto, requesting confirmation that Buhari was an alumnus. In response, Carlo Villanueva, an official of the Institution wrote, \u201c''Regarding your request for confirmation of degree for Mr Ibrahim Salisu Buhari. We have searched our records and could not find anybody with the name you are inquiring with.''\u201d\n\nHe had been found guilty in the court of public opinion and among in the halls where policies are made and sentences are meted out, the tension had reached a fever pitch.\n\nIn 23 July 1999, disgraced and cornered, Buhari faced [[Nigerians]] and admitted to falsifying his age and forging certificates as well as other contents of the News report.\n\n\u201c''I apologize to you. I apologize to the nation. I apologize to my family and friends for all the distress I have caused them. I was misled in error by zeal to serve the nation, I hope the nation will forgive me and give me the opportunity to serve again.''\u201d\n\nHe resigned from his membership of the House of Representatives in 1999.\n\nIn 2013, he was chosen as part of the governing council of the [[University of Nigeria]] by the [[Federal government of Nigeria|Nigerian government]].<ref name=\"saharareporters\">{{cite news|url=http://saharareporters.com/2013/07/05/salisu-buhari-member-unn-governing-council-no-please|title=Salisu Buhari, A Member of UNN Governing Council? No Please!|last=Igbokwe|first=Joe|date=5 July 2013|work=[[Sahara Reporters]]|accessdate=5 September 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"nigeriapoliticsonline\">{{cite web|url=http://nigeriapoliticsonline.com/tinubu-guilty-of-certificate-forgery-like-salisu-buhari-obasanjo/|title=Tinubu guilty of certificate forgery like Salisu Buhari  &#8211;Obasanjo|date=14 August 2013|website=Nigeria Politics Online|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140905053505/http://nigeriapoliticsonline.com/tinubu-guilty-of-certificate-forgery-like-salisu-buhari-obasanjo/|archivedate=5 September 2014|url-status=dead|accessdate=5 September 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"9jabook\">{{cite web|url=http://www.9jabook.com/forum/topics/disgraced-fmr-speaker-salisu-buhari-of-toronto-university-forged-|title=Disgraced Fmr Speaker Salisu Buhari of &quot;Toronto University forged certificate&quot;  Now in UNN Governing council|date=4 April 2013|website=9jabook|accessdate=5 September 2014}}</ref>{{Unreliable source?|date=July 2018}}<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/africa/401123.stm|title=World: Africa {{!}} Nigerian speaker quits in tears|date=22 July 1999|work=[[BBC News]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thescoopng.com/abati-defends-appointment-of-certificate-forger-salisu-buhari-as-unn-governing-council-member/|title=Abati defends appointment of certificate forger, Salisu Buhari, as UNN governing council member|last=Lawal|first=Dare|date=14 April 2013|website=The ScoopNG}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}https://www.pulse.ng/gist/pop-culture/the-story-of-salisu-buhari-and-the-toronto-university-saga-id8022958.html\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Buhari, Salisu}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:University of Nigeria, Nsukka people]]\n", "name_user": "QWEDB", "label": "safe", "comment": "Increased Clarity", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Salisu_Buhari"}
{"title_page": "Li Xian (actor)", "text_new": "{{short description|Chinese actor}}\n{{Chinese name|[[Li (surname \u674e)|Li]]}}\n{{infobox person\n| name               = Li Xian\n| image              = Li Xian Chinese Actor.png\n| caption            = Li Xian interviewed by Hotpot TV on July, 2019\n| native_name        = {{linktext|\u674e\u73b0}}\n| native_name_lang   = zh\n| pronunciation      = L\u01d0 Xi\u00e0n\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1991|10|19}}\n| birth_place        = [[Xianning]], [[Hubei]]\n| nationality        = Chinese\n| alma_mater         = [[Beijing Film Academy]]\n| occupation         = Actor\n| years_active       = 2011\u2013present\n| agent              = Easy Entertainment\n| module             = {{Infobox Chinese|child=yes|order=st\n| t= \u674e\u73fe | s= {{linktext|\u674e|\u73b0}} \n  | p = L\u01d0 Xi\u00e0n\n}}\n}}\n'''Li Xian''' ({{zh|s=\u674e\u73b0}}; born 19 October 1991)<ref name=\"The Beijing News\">{{cite news |last1=Liu |first1=Wei |title=Li Xian really wants to buy a cup of coffee |url=http://epaper.bjnews.com.cn/html/2019-12/17/content_774177.htm?div=-1 |accessdate=1 April 2020 |work=[[The Beijing News]] |publisher=The Beijing News |archiveurl=http://epaper.bjnews.com.cn/html/2019-12/17/content_774177.htm?div=-1/|archivedate=April 2, 2020|date=December 17, 2019 |pages=C04 |language=zh}}</ref> is a [[Mainland China]] actor. He made his feature film debut in 2011, and is best known for his roles in the drama ''[[Go Go Squid!]]''.<ref name=xian>{{cite web |last1=Yau |first1=Elaine |title=Who is Li Xian, rising star of China TV hit Go Go Squid? |url=https://www.scmp.com/lifestyle/entertainment/article/3021194/who-li-xian-rising-star-chinas-go-go-squid-hit-television |website=South China Morning Post |accessdate=1 April 2020|archiveurl=https://www.scmp.com/lifestyle/entertainment/article/3021194/who-li-xian-rising-star-chinas-go-go-squid-hit-television|archivedate=August 5, 2019 |language=en |date=August 4, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nLi Xian was born as Li Han ({{zh|s=\u674e\u73fe}}) on 19 October 1991 in [[Xianning]] City, and grew up in [[Jingzhou]] City, [[Hubei]] Province.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.sina.com.cn/ku/star_info_index.d.html?id=fyhvyie0226195|title=Li Xian Profile|website=Sina|language=zh}}</ref>  He studied at Jingzhou Middle School one of the best school in the City. In 2009 he thought to study STEM subjects in college, but after failing the annual college entrance examination, he took the test again and enter the 2010 Department of [[Beijing Film Academy]] Performance Department.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.ifeng.com/a/20160402/48317189_0.shtml||title=Jingzhou chubby turned into a half-cooked male god|script-title=zh:\u56fe\u6587\uff1a\u8346\u5dde\u5c0f\u80d6\u53d8\u8eab\u534a\u719f\u7537\u795e|website=ifeng|publisher=Chutian Metropolis Daily|date=April 2, 2016|language=zh}}</ref> For the convenience of entry, Li changed his name \"{{zh|s=\u665b}}\" into Xian \"{{zh|s=\u73b0}}\" which is mean \"present\".<ref name=\"The Beijing News\"/>  And he was also the first college student to be admitted to the academy in Jingzhou, Hubei Province.\n\n==Career==\n===2011\u20132018: Acting debut and Rising popularity===\nIn 2011, Li made his debut in director Wang Jing's film, \"A Thousand Arrows Through Heart\" in which he played Li Baoli's son Xiaobao, a boy who is full of resentment towards his mother and has a restrained voice because of his father's early death. He got his first role in [[Feng Shui (2012 film)|''Feng Shui'']] when he was a sophomore at the academy. He got the role due to his age and the fact that the director, who was affiliated with the academy, was looking for someone from Hubei province, where Li was from.''<ref name=\"feng\">{{cite web|url=http://www.jznews.com.cn/comnews/system/2013/02/22/010784530.shtml|date=February 22, 2013|website=JZ News|language=zh|script-title=zh:\u300a\u4e07\u7bad\u7a7f\u5fc3\u300b\"\u5c0f\u5b9d\" \u6625\u8282\u56de\u8346\u5dde\u62dc\u5e74}}</ref>'' In 2013, he starred in the romance teen flick ''[[Singing When We're Young]]'', produced by [[Andy Lau]].<ref name=sing>{{cite web|url=http://www.rbc.cn/bobo/2013-07/31/cms29689article.shtml|script-title=zh:\u4e13\u8bbf\u300a\u521d\u604b\u672a\u6ee1\u300b\u5bfc\u6f14\u674e\u5a1f\u3001\u6f14\u5458\u674e\u73b0|date=July 31, 2013|publisher=Radio Beijing Corporation |language=zh-cn}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, Li made his small-screen debut in the omnibus web drama ''[[City of Fantasy]]''.<ref name=city>{{cite web|url=http://ent.163.com/14/1029/12/A9NLMTKS000333J5.html|script-title=zh:\u674e\u73b0\u300a\u5947\u5999\u4e16\u7eaa\u300b\u732e\u8367\u5e55\u521d\u543b \u6f14\u6280\u5927\u53d7\u597d\u8bc4|date=October 29, 2014|website=Netease|language=zh}}</ref>\nIn 2015, he co-starred with Chen Xiao, Du Tianhao and Liu Ruilin in the coming-of-age brotherhood web series ''[[Who Sleeps My Bro]]''.<ref name=sleep1>{{cite web|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/micro-reading/2016-03/28/content_24142835.htm|script-title=zh:\u300a\u7761\u5728\u6211\u4e0a\u94fa\u7684\u5144\u5f1f\u300b\u674e\u73b0\u51fa\u90535\u5e74\u5e05\u6c14\u8d70\u7ea2|date=March 28, 2016|website=China Daily|language=zh}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.ifeng.com/a/20160201/42571343_0.shtml|script-title=zh:\u300a\u7761\u5728\u6211\u4e0a\u94fa\u7684\u5144\u5f1f\u300b\u6b63\u80fd\u91cf\u9752\u6625\u5267\u4e00\u6837\u662f|website=ifeng|date=February 1, 2016|language=zh}}</ref> The series was later adapted into a film starring the original cast. In the same year he participated in the Shanghai International Film Festival Red Carpet.<ref name=sleep>{{cite web|url=http://ent.ifeng.com/a/20151216/42545751_0.shtml|script-title=zh:\u300a\u7761\u5728\u6211\u4e0a\u94fa\u7684\u5144\u5f1f\u300b\u5b9a\u68634\u67081\u65e5 \u70ed\u8840\u9752\u6625\u71c3\u503c\u7206\u8868|website=ifeng|date=December 16, 2015|language=zh}}</ref> In the same year Li co-starred alongside [[Zhang Ruoyun]] and [[Jiao Junyan]] in the crime medical web drama ''[[Medical Examiner Dr. Qin]]'' as the criminal police captain Lin Tao,<ref name=qin>{{cite web|url=http://ent.163.com/16/1018/12/C3LMKDV3000380EO.html|script-title=zh:\u300a\u6cd5\u533b\u79e6\u660e\u300b\u83b7\u8d5e\u4e0b\u996d\u5267 \u674e\u73b0\"\u4e09\u526f\u8138\u5b54\"\u53cd\u5dee\u840c_\u7f51\u6613\u5a31\u4e50|website=Netease|date=October 18, 2016|language=zh}}</ref> which was acclaimed for both its storyline and performance.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bjnews.com.cn/ent/2016/11/25/424878.html|script-title=zh:\u6f14\u5458\u65b0\u52bf\u529b\u4e28\u674e\u73b0\uff1a\u521a\u62cd\u300a\u6cd5\u533b\u79e6\u660e\u300b\uff0c\u8fd8\u633a\"\u5012\u80c3\u53e3\"\u7684|date=November 25, 2016|website=Beijing News|language=zh}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/culture/2016-12/14/content_27663593.htm|title=Behind the success of 'Medical Examiner Dr. Qin'|work=China Daily|date=December 14, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.globaltimes.cn/content/1023044.shtml|title=Sohu TV drama \u2018Medical Examiner Dr. Qin\u2019 receives more than 1.2 billion views|work=Global Times|date=December 11, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, he co-starred with [[Angelababy]], [[Jing Bairan]], and [[Bai Yu (actor)|Bai Yu]] in the romantic movie \"[[Love O2O (film)|Love O2O]]\", and played the roommate of the leading actor Xiao Nai, Yu Banshan in the film. In December, he starred in the music video of [[Zhang Jiao]]'s \" I'm Jiang Xiaobai 2016 \" and also starred in the second edition MV of [[Luhan]]\u2019s Medal.\n\nIn 2017, his web drama ''[[Tientsin Mystic]]'' which was broadcast internationally on [[Netflix]]<ref name=tien>{{cite web|url=https://news.china.com/news100/11038989/20170706/30927237.html|script-title=zh:\u300a\u6cb3\u795e\u300b\u5b9a\u6863719 \"\u987d\u75de\u6cb3\u795e\"\u674e\u73b0\u8d64\u8eab\u79c0\u6c34\u6027|date=July 6, 2017|website=China.com|language=zh}}</ref> made him received a lot of praise for his acting, and also accumulated his first fans for him. The job offer he received was one year in a row, and in order to enter the role attentively, he refused other jobs during the filming.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/a/201804/18/WS5ad68c6aa3105cdcf6518e5c.html|title=Dramatic improvement |website=China Daily|date=April 18, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.sina.com.cn/o/2017-08-17/doc-ifykcqav9367088.shtml|title=Li Xian: Not how handsome I am, but Guo Deyou is very handsome |script-title=zh:\u4e13\u8bbf\uff5c\u674e\u73b0\uff1a\u4e0d\u662f\u6211\u591a\u5e05\uff0c\u662f\u90ed\u5f97\u53cb\u5f88\u5e05|date=August 17, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200413155028/http://news.sina.com.cn/o/2017-08-17/doc-ifykcqav9367088.shtml |archivedate=April 13, 2020|website=Sina|language=zh}}</ref>\nIn 2018, Li starred in the romance drama  ''[[Only Side by Side with You]]'' as a special forces agent.<ref name=side>{{cite web|url=http://ent.sina.com.cn/v/m/2017-04-07/doc-ifyecezv2449403.shtml|script-title=zh:\u300a\u5357\u65b9\u6709\u4e54\u6728\u300b\u66dd\u9635\u5bb9 \u9648\u4f1f\u9706\u674e\u73b0\u4e0a\u6f14\u5236\u670d\u8bf1\u60d1|website=Sina|language=zh|date=April 7, 2017}}</ref> In the same year his film ''Science and Sensibility'' released.\n\n===2019\u2013present: Breakthrough===\n{{Quote box | width=30% | align=left| quote=\"Want to be an actor? Want to be an artist? Or want to be a star? Or You need to say all three. Then when you do these things, you need to give them the corresponding time and energy. For me, I think I might want to be an actor, which is a more important thing.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Zeng |first1=Le |title=\"Go Go Squid!\" Li Xian: The only thing you can do is to be yourself |url=http://ent.people.com.cn/n1/2019/0714/c1012-31232476.html |script-title=zh:\u300a\u4eb2\u7231\u7684\uff0c\u70ed\u7231\u7684\u300b\u674e\u73b0\uff1a\u552f\u4e00\u80fd\u505a\u7684\u5c31\u662f\u505a\u597d\u81ea\u5df1--\u4eba\u6c11\u7f51\u5a31\u4e50\u9891\u9053