ive To The Future (Gei Wei Lai)'' charted on Billboard China Social Chart as well as [[Billboard China Top 100]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=China |first1=Billboard |title=Billboard China Top 100 - The Week of August 9, 2019 |url=http://www.billboardchina.cn/top/top100/2019-09-06.html |website=www.billboardchina.cn |publisher=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=4 April 2020 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190809183016/http://www.billboardchina.cn/top/top100/2019-08-09.html |archivedate=August 9, 2019 |language=zh}}</ref> for 10 weeks and peak at 7.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Billboard |title=Billboard China Social Chart - The week of October 5, 2019 |url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/billboard-china-social-chart/2019-10-05 |accessdate=April 4, 2020 |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200404033934/https://www.billboard.com/charts/billboard-china-social-chart/2019-10-05 |archivedate=April 4, 2020 |language=en}}</ref> Li made a cameo appeareance as [[Air Traffic Controller]] in the chinese film [[The Captain (2019 film)|The Captain]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Chao |first1=Teng |title=Li Xian, Huang Zhizhong, Zhu Yawen appeared in \"China Captain\" to form \"behind the scenes\" support |script-title=zh:=\u674e\u73b0\u9ec4\u5fd7\u5fe0\u6731\u4e9a\u6587\u73b0\u8eab\u300a\u4e2d\u56fd\u673a\u957f\u300b\u7ec4\u6210\u201c\u5e55\u540e\u201d\u652f\u63f4 |url=http://www.bjnews.com.cn/ent/2019/09/24/628912.html |accessdate=April 6, 2020 |work=[[Beijing News]] |date=September 24, 2020 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200204205058/http://www.bjnews.com.cn/ent/2019/09/24/628912.html |archivedate=February 4, 2020 |language=zh}}</ref> The same year, he starred in the iQIYI's costume-drama ''[[Sword Dynasty]]'' as Ding Ning, produced by [[Feng Xiaogang]]. He sing the soundtrack of ''Red Fox Scholar'', titled ''Glorious Future (Qian Cheng Si jin)'' with [[Chen Linong]] and peak at 8 on Billboard China Social Chart<ref>